<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-18T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/182: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-18T16:00:00+08:00">November 18, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:20 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1004. Legation’s 1000, November 14, 8 p.m. Following telegram has been
                            received from Jacobs and Bucknell: “Pending further instructions from
                            Legation, we shall not proceed to Nanking. Similar action is being taken
                            by other delegates”, which I have telegraphically approved.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>